channel.title: I need help getting onto myspace
channel.description: The only way for me to get on the computer is at the libary but they have a block on some sites including myspace. So i was wondering if anyone knew how to get around that? all it is some at&t blocker. Please help.

item.title: I need help getting onto myspace
item.dc:creator: @bloodrayne bloodrayne
item.description:
@bloodrayne wrote:

bobthecat:

use command prompt… if the computer doesn’t have it go into notepad and type “Command” then save it as a .bat file. Then open it…type in “ping www.myscape.com” and hit enter you should get the ip address of the site. then go onto the internet and type in the ip adress.

Most site blockers these days block the IP address the computer connects to anyways, so… I doubt using the IP would work. It doesn’t work at my school at least ;l

item.title: I need help getting onto myspace
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

[quote=“Tico135, post:8, topic:210351”][quote author=Zoss link=topic=277246.msg2260272#msg2260272 date=1212582485]

Most schools run on a proxy which limits the webpages you can access. Use a proxy and you should be allowed to access it without a problem.

How about, if, they are using a application which you must use to connect to their own proxy servers and all searches/data that is sent/received is scanned for phrases, such as Myspace?
[/quote]

Actually, now that I think of it, it actually blocks the port, it doesn’t scan for certain phrases, as that would be quite hard. Especially for them to block sites such as mopar, because they don’t know about them. Therefore your theory is highly un-likely and a false statement.[/quote]

My school blocks on phrases, and also mopar is blocked at school.
